$ System.IO.Path::IsPathRooted()

{ PowerShell example

  The following simple → Windows/PowerShell script uses `IsPathRooted` to check if the passed → Windows/PowerShell/language/statement/function/parameters[parameter] is an absolute or relatie path.

  gh|.NET-API|/System/IO/Path/IsPathRooted.ps1||

  Note that `IsPathRooted()` does not verify if the actual path actually exists.

  Compare with the `-isAbsolute` option of the → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/path/split[cmdLet `split-path`].

}
